highlightText: '## Summary  - PyTorch can be considered as numpy on GPU for neural networks - PyTorch provides different data types     - float is a good default value (good balance between necessary precision, performance and memory usage) - PyTorch can run on different devices     - GPU is used for running neural networks     - CPU is used for data loading and other intensive tasks - We should write device agnostic code (basics shown here) - We should inherit from torch.nn.
